{{Merge to|Great Retreat (Serbian)|discuss=Talk:Great Retreat (Serbian)#Proposed merge of Massacres of Albanians during the Great Retreat into Great Retreat (Serbian)|date=March 2020}} '''Massacres of Albanians during the Great Retreat''' ([[Albanian language|Alb]]. ''Masakrat ndaj shqiptarevë gjat tërheqjes e ushtrisë sërbe'') were massacres, crimes and pillaging which soldiers in the Serbian army committed against the Albanian civil population during the [[Great Retreat (Serbian)|Great Retreat]] in 1915.<ref>{{cite book |last1=William W. |first1=Hagen |title=The Balkans' Lethal Nationalisms. Foreign Affairs, Vol. 78, No. 4 (Jul. - Aug., 1999), pp. 52-64 |publisher=Council on Foreign Relations |page=58 |edition="Slavic Christians (mostly Serbs and Montenegrins) perpetrated terrible massacres of Muslim Albanians, along with Turks and Slavophone Muslims, in Kosovo, Montenegro, Bosnia, and southern Serbia during and immediately after World War" |url=https://resolvenet.org/system/files/2018-11/hagen.pdf}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Stevenson |first1=David |title=1914-1918: The History of the First World War |date=2004 |publisher=Penguin Books Limited |isbn=978-0-14-190434-4 |url=https://books.google.se/books?id=OlN6GIAlsqMC&pg=PR364&dq=Serbian+retreat+1915+Albanians&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwidneGb0bzoAhVB1qYKHXLTCN84HhDoAQhZMAY#v=onepage&q=Albanians&f=false |accessdate=28 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Në Shqipëri ekspozitë për "humbjet” serbe më 1915. Propaganda për vdekjen 200 mijë serbëve! |url=https://www.balkanweb.com/ne-shqiperi-ekspozite-per-humbjet-serbe-me-1915-propaganda-per-vdekjen-200-mije-serbeve/ |work=Balkanweb.com - News24 |issue=Translation: "A story that through the photos can at least show a unique testimony to the history of the First World War in the Balkans," says Tare. But the truth is that this withdrawal is done in three directions, killing and massacring Albanians wherever Serbs go. |date=16 September 2015 |language=sq-AL}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Kur serbët tërhiqeshin në vitet 1915 nga tokat shqiptare!? |url=https://sot.com.al/opinione/kur-serbët-tërhiqeshin-në-vitet-1915-nga-tokat-shqiptare |work=sot.com.al |issue=Nga Besi BEKTESHI Viti 1915 ka qenë momenti kur serbët kanë lënë disa mijra të vdekur në luftën e tyre me perandorinë austro-hungareze. Një pjesë e rëndësishme e territorit ku kanë lënë eshtrat e tyre, ishte pikërisht territori shqiptar. Por, ata më përpara kanë bërë masakra të padëgjuara në trevat shqiptare, ndër shqiptarë të lindur në këto treva dhe pa dallim feje në çdo rast.}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=PhD. Cand |first1=Ma. Veli Kryeziu, |title=Albanians in Confrontation with the Challenges of World War I. International Journal of Humanities and Social Science |date=2019 |publisher=Public University “Hasan Prishtina“ No.31, 10 000 |location=Prishtina, Republic of Kosovo |page=90 |edition="In January 1915, under the direction of Hasan Prishtina, the rebellion was extended up to Gjakova’s highlands (Rushiti, 2003:169); from where Serb forces were forced to retreat leaving behind the traces of crime committed against the civilian population" |url=https://www.ijhssnet.com/journals/Vol_9_No_7_July_2019/11.pdf |accessdate=28 March 2020 |language=English |format=PDF |chapter=Vol. 9, No. 7}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Tallon |first1=James N. |title=ARTICLES AND ANALYSES: ALBANIA’S LONG WORLD WAR I (1912–1925) |date=2014 |publisher=Lewis University. STUDIA HISTORYCZNE R. LVII, 2014, Z. 4 (228) PL ISSN 0025-1429 |pages=443-444 |edition=his created animosity between Albanians and the retreating Allies, significantly increasing violence between Albanians and Serbs who were viewed as invaders. |url=https://www.academia.edu/17606975/Albanias_Long_World_War_I_1912-1925_Albania_in_WWI?auto=download |accessdate=28 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Shkelzën |first1=Gashi |title=The History of Kosovo in the history textbooks of Kosovo, Albania, Serbia, Montenegro and Macedonia |date=2016 |publisher=Alter Habitus |location=Pristina |page=83 |edition=At the end of 1915, after attacks by Austro-Hungarian forces, Serbian and Montenegrin forces were forced to withdraw from Kosovo. They withdrew to Greece through Kosovo, Montenegro and Albania. During the withdrawal through Albanian land they committed crimes of pillaging and more serious crimes against the Albanian people |url=http://kfos.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Historia_e_Kosoves_SHG_ENG.pdf |accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>
